The paper focuses on using machine vision techniques for human activity recognition using photoplethysmography sensor data. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms such as support vector machines, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which falls under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of sensor data, which falls under the signal processing (cs.SD) sub-category.
